<topic id="creating-new-documents">
  <title>Creating New Documents and Templates</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Creating new documents</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> includes a helpful <uicontrol>New Document</uicontrol> wizard that
      allows you to customize and create new files from a large list of document types and
      predefined templates. You can also create your own templates and share them with others.</p>
    <p>To quickly create a new document:<ol>
        <li>Click the <ph product="author developer editor"><uicontrol><image
                href="../img/New16.png" id="image_hy1_zdp_sr"/>New</uicontrol> button on the toolbar
            or select <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>New</uicontrol>
            </menucascade></ph><ph product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
                ><uicontrol><image href="../img/EclipseNew.png" id="image_nbd_fkf_wr"
              />New</uicontrol> button on the toolbar or select <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>New</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Other</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol keyref="product"/>
            </menucascade></ph>.</li>
        <li>Select the type of document that you want to create.<note type="tip">You can use the
            text filter field at the top of the dialog box to search for a specific
          template.</note></li>
        <li product="author developer editor">Click the <uicontrol>Create</uicontrol> button at the
          bottom of the dialog box.</li>
        <li product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">Click the
            <uicontrol>Next</uicontrol> button, then <uicontrol>Finish</uicontrol>.</li>
      </ol></p>
  </body>
</topic>
